@section standard_app_encoding Encoding Helpers

@subsection standard_app_encoding_base58 Base58

<b>Files:</b> `base58.h`, `base58.c`

Bitcoin Base58 alphabet encode/decode.

| Function | Description |
|---|---|
| @ref base58_encode() "base58_encode(in, in_len, out, out_len)" | Binary → Base58 string; returns character count or -1. Max input: `MAX_ENC_INPUT_SIZE` (120 bytes). |
| @ref base58_decode() "base58_decode(in, in_len, out, out_len)" | Base58 string → binary; returns byte count or -1. Max input: `MAX_DEC_INPUT_SIZE` (164 chars). |

Leading zero bytes are encoded as the `'1'` character (Bitcoin convention).

@subsection standard_app_encoding_varint Variable-length integer (varint)

<b>Files:</b> `varint.h`, `varint.c`

Bitcoin-protocol variable-length integer (1/3/5/9 bytes).

| Function | Description |
|---|---|
| @ref varint_size() "varint_size(value)" | Returns the serialised byte count for `value`. |
| @ref varint_read() "varint_read(in, in_len, value)" | Parses a varint; returns bytes consumed or -1. |
| @ref varint_write() "varint_write(out, offset, value)" | Writes a varint at `out + offset`; returns bytes written or -1. |

@subsection standard_app_encoding_readwrite Low-level integer read/write

<b>Files:</b> `read.h`, `read.c`, `write.h`, `write.c`

Bounds-unchecked integer accessors used internally by `buffer.c` and `varint.c`.
All functions take a `(ptr, offset)` pair and read/write big-endian or little-endian
integers of width 16, 32, or 64 bits.

@note Callers are responsible for ensuring
sufficient buffer space.

<br>

